1 WHEREAS, for the Forty-Fourth Annual Irish-Italian Parade, Senate President
2 Cameron Henry, Jr. was selected as the 2026 Irish Grand Marshal and Erik Youngblood was
3 selected as the 2026 Italian Grand Marshal; and
4 WHEREAS, for the first time in parade history, the Louisiana State University Tiger
5 Marching Band, also known as the Golden Band from Tigerland and a true crowd pleaser,
6 made a roaring appearance to lead Grand Marshals Henry and Youngblood in the parade;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, Senate President Cameron Henry's leadership, dedication to public
9 service, and commitment to the people of Louisiana made him a fitting choice for the
10 distinguished honor of serving as the 2026 Irish Grand Marshal.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
12 does hereby commend Senate President Cameron Henry, Jr. for serving as the 2026 Irish
13 Grand Marshal in the Forty-Fourth Annual Irish-Italian Parade in Metairie, Louisiana.
